Ya kamata Amurka ta ninka yawan kuɗin da take kashewa a kan AI.
Yayin da China ke kara aiki a fannin ilimin kere kere, Amurka ta kamata ta ninka yawan kudaden da take kashewa a fannin binciken kere kere, in ji Kai-Fu Lee, mai saka jari da kuma kwararren masaniyar kere kere wanda ya yi aiki a Google, Microsoft da Apple.
Wannan bayanin ya zo ne bayan da wasu daga cikin Gwamnatin Amurka suka sanar da matakan AI, duk da cewa kasar ba ta da wata dabara ta AI.
A wannan lokacin, kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirinta a bara: tana da burin zama kasa ta daya a duniya wajen kirkire-kirkire a fannin AI nan da shekarar 2030.
Abin da zai taimaka wajen samun ci gaba a fannin AI shi ne ninki biyu na kasafin kudin da ake kashewa wajen gudanar da bincike, saboda sauran kasashen duniya sun yi nisa da Amurka, kuma muna son mu zama masu jagorantar ci gaban da za a samu a fannin AI, in ji Lee.
A ninka kudade zai ninka damar Amurka ta cimma babban ci gaba a AI, Lee ya shaida wa CNBC a wata hira da aka yi a wannan makon.
Lee, marubucin littafin nan AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World Order, wanda Houghton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shi ne babban darektan kamfanin Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a Face++, daya daga cikin manyan kamfanonin AI a kasar Sin.
A cikin 1980 ya yi aiki a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon a cikin tsarin AI wanda ya wuce ɗan wasan Amurka na Othello tare da mafi kyawun matsayi kuma, daga baya, ya yi aiki a matsayin mai zartarwa a Microsoft Research kuma a matsayin shugaban reshen China na Google.
Lee ya yi farin ciki da gasar fasaha ta gwamnatin Amurka, irin su Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA) Robotics Challenge, kuma ya yi mamakin lokacin da za a yi na gaba don gano masu hangen nesa na gaba.
