Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da zaluntar kanta da "tallace-tallacen farfaganda".
Mako guda bayan wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata sanarwa mai shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka da ke tallata fa'idodin cinikayya tsakanin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafofin yada labaran Amurka don yada farfaganda.
Shugaba Donald Trump ya yi jawabi a ranar Laraba da ta gabata ga jaridar China Daily da ke buga jaridar The Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi kowanne a jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi China da tsoma baki a zaben majalisar dokokin Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi cewa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fadawa Reuters cewa wani sabon mataki ne na yakin Washington na kara matsa lamba kan China.
Duk da cewa al'ada ce ga gwamnatocin kasashen waje su sanya tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwanci, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin yakin cinikayya wanda ke kara tsanantawa kuma ya ga karuwar haraji kan shigo da kayayyaki.
Kudaden haraji na China a farkon yakin cinikayya an yi niyyar hukunta masu fitar da kaya daga jihohi kamar Iowa, wadanda ke goyon bayan Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump, a cewar masana kasar Sin da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa na dogon lokaci, babban mai fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya yi iƙirarin cewa Beijing ta cutar da ma'aikata, manoma da kamfanonin Amurka.
A wani rahoto da ya wallafa a jaridar The Des Moines Register, Branstad ya rubuta cewa, "yana kara tsanantawa ta hanyar buga tallace-tallace a jaridarmu ta kyauta".
"A cikin yada farfagandarsu, gwamnatin kasar Sin tana amfani da ƙaunatacciyar al'adar Amurka ta 'yancin faɗar albarkacin baki da' yan jarida kyauta ta hanyar sanya tallan da aka biya a The Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A gefe guda kuma, a cikin kiosk da ke kan titin nan a Beijing, za ku ga 'yan muryoyin da ke nuna bambanci kuma ba za ku ga ainihin ra'ayoyin da' yan kasar Sin za su iya yi game da yanayin tattalin arzikin kasar Sin ba, saboda kafofin watsa labarai suna karkashin rinjayar jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta kasar Sin", in ji shi.
Ya kara da cewa "wani daga cikin manyan jaridu a kasar Sin ya kauce wa tayin buga" labarinsa, amma bai bayyana sunan littafin ba.
